lisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/turkey-student-visa-financial-qualification-conditions-and-application-sureci.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/turkey-student-visa-financial-qualification-conditions-and-application-sureci.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"On-campus and off-campus living cost comparison for students in Turkey showing accommodation, food, and transportation expenses.","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/cost-of-living-on-and-off-campus-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/cost-of-living-on-and-off-campus-in-turkey/","name":"On-Campus and Off-Campus Cost of Living Turkey","datePublished":"2025-08-27T17:43:49+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:51:54+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/turkey-student-visa-financial-qualification-conditions-and-application-sureci.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"On-Campus and Off-Campus Cost of Living Turkey","keywords":"Cost of Living","datePublished":"2025-08-27T17:43:49+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:51:54+03:00","articleSection":"Cost of Living and Accommodation","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Explore the cost of living on and off campus. Read our article to find out which option is best for you!","name":"On-Campus and Off-Campus Cost of Living Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/cost-of-living-on-and-off-campus-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/cost-of-living-on-and-off-campus-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/turkey-student-visa-financial-qualification-conditions-and-application-sureci.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/cost-of-living-on-and-off-campus-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In recent years, Turkey has come to the fore for international students not only for its well-established educational institutions and cultural diversity, but also for its affordable living costs. On-campus and off-campus living options for students are critical for both budget planning and social adaptation. In this article, we provide a detailed guide for students to create a realistic budget plan by comparing the costs of on-campus accommodation, food, transportation and basic needs with the financial dynamics of off-campus life in Turkey.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="costs-of-living-in-turkey-on-and-off-campus-comparison">Cost of Living in Turkey: On and Off Campus Comparison</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">On-campus living refers to accommodation options usually offered in university dormitories or on campus. Off-campus living refers to students living in apartments or houses around the university.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="costs-of-living-on-campus">Cost of Living on Campus</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">On-campus living often offers a more organized and secure environment. However, costs should also be taken into consideration. Accommodation fees in university dormitories in Turkey usually range between 150-300 USD per month. This price may vary depending on the facilities offered by the dormitories and the cost of living in the city.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="off-campus-living-costs">Off-Campus Living Costs</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Although off-campus living offers students more freedom and independence, it can vary more in terms of costs. For example, if a student wants to rent an apartment in the city center, the monthly rent can range from 300-600 USD. In addition, when invoices and other expenses are taken into account, total costs can increase.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also benefit from our article on <a href="https://roadtostudy.com"><span data-sheets-root="1">Pros and Cons of Different Types of Accommodation in Turkey</span></a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="student-budget-and-lifestyle-on-campus-vs-off-campus">Student Budget and Lifestyle: On Campus vs. Off Campus</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Students&#8217; lifestyles greatly affect their budgets. On-campus living provides opportunities to participate in social activities, while off-campus living allows for more independence and personal space.</p>


<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Feature</th>
<th>Campus Life</th>
<th>Life Off Campus</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Social Interaction</strong></td>
<td>Easy way to meet other students and participate in social activities</td>
<td>More limited social interaction, more contact with locals</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Security</strong></td>
<td>General 24/7 security and controlled entry and exit</td>
<td>Depends on neighborhood security, additional security measures may be required</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Ease of Access</strong></td>
<td>Walking distance to classrooms, library and campus amenities</td>
<td>Transportation may require time and additional budget</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Cost</strong></td>
<td>Prepaid package price (dorm+food), few unexpected costs</td>
<td>There may be additional costs such as rent, utility bills, dues</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Freedom and Flexibility</strong></td>
<td>Campus rules require compliance, visitor restrictions may apply</td>
<td>Freedom to set your own rules, more flexible living</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Comfort and Space</strong></td>
<td>Standard room layouts, common areas</td>
<td>Personalized spaces, more living space</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also take a look at <a href="https://roadtostudy.com"><span data-sheets-root="1">Trusted Sources and Platforms When Looking for a House to Rent in Turkey</span></a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="advantages-and-disadvantages-of-on-campus-life-in-turkey">Advantages and Disadvantages of On-Campus Life in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Campus life offers many advantages, but also some disadvantages. It can make students&#8217; educational lives more enjoyable, especially as it offers a rich environment for social interaction. However, disadvantages such as high costs and limited freedom can be a problem for some students.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="life-off-campus-freedom-and-cost-balance">Life Off Campus: Freedom and Cost Balance</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Off-campus living offers students independence and personal space, but requires careful planning of costs. By considering accommodation options that fit their budget, students can maintain their freedom and keep their costs under control.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="choose-the-most-suitable-option-for-you">Choose the Most Suitable Option for You!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Choosing between on-campus and off-campus living in Türkiye depends on students&#8217; lifestyles and budgets. On-campus living offers social interaction and security, while off-campus living provides greater freedom and independence. It&#8217;s important for students to choose the option that best suits their needs and budget. If you&#8217;re considering studying in Türkiye, take action!</p>


<div class="dad65929">
<div class="_4f9bf79 d7dc56a8 _43c05b5">
<div class="ds-markdown ds-markdown--block">
<h2 class="ds-markdown-paragraph">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3 class="ds-markdown-paragraph">What is the average monthly cost of living for students in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="ds-markdown-paragraph">The average monthly cost of living for a student ranges between <strong>320-600 USD</strong>, covering accommodation, transportation, food, basic necessities, and social expenses. In major cities like Istanbul, costs can rise to <strong>480-800 USD</strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<h3 class="ds-markdown-paragraph">How are on-campus and off-campus accommodation costs?</h3>


<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>On-campus dormitories: Monthly <strong>80-200 USD</strong></li>



<li>Off-campus room/house for rent: <strong>200-350 USD</strong></li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-much-does-transportation-cost">How much does transportation cost?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The monthly cost with a student transportation card is between <strong>30-48 USD</strong>. Additional transportation options such as using a taxi or car can increase the cost by <strong>20-80 USD</strong>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-much-to-budget-for-food-and-groceries">How much to budget for food and groceries</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Monthly food and groceries: <strong>160-280 USD</strong></li>



<li>Meal at campus dining hall: <strong>1.6-2.8 USD</strong></li>



<li>Restaurant food: <strong>5-10 USD</strong></li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-much-are-the-additional-costs-health-social-activities-course-materials">How much are the additional costs (health, social activities, course materials)</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Health insurance (annual): <strong>80-160 USD</strong></li>



<li>Social activities (monthly): <strong>40-80 USD</strong></li>



<li>Textbooks and materials (semester): <strong>40-120 USD</strong></li>
</ul>



