 working with real estate agents in Turkey. Armed with the information, make the right choice!","name":"Things to Consider When Working with Real Estate Agents","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/working-with-real-estate-agents/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/working-with-real-estate-agents/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/things-to-consider-when-working-with-real-estate-agents.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/working-with-real-estate-agents/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Starting your education in Turkey is an exciting journey! A new city, new friends and of course a new living space await you. Taking the right steps when it comes to accommodation can make the process much easier and more enjoyable. Knowing which documents you need and what to look out for, especially when working with real estate agents, saves both time and energy. In this article, we have compiled everything you need to know for a hassle-free stay in Turkey.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-to-consider-when-choosing-a-real-estate-agent-in-turkey">What to Consider When Choosing a Real Estate Agent in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Choosing a real estate agent is one of the most critical stages of the real estate buying and selling process. Finding the right real estate agent provides great advantages in terms of both time and cost. You can make the right choice by paying attention to the following points:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>License and Certificates:</strong> Check whether the real estate agent is licensed. In Turkey, real estate agents must be affiliated to the Turkish Federation of Realtors.</li>



<li><strong>Experience:</strong> The experience of the real estate agent in the sector directly affects the quality of the service they will offer you. Real estate agents who have been in the sector for many years usually have more knowledge and experience.</li>



<li><strong>References:</strong> Ask for references from previous clients. This will give you an idea about the reliability of the real estate agent.</li>



<li><strong>Communication Skills:</strong> The real estate agent&#8217;s communication skills determine how smoothly the process will go. It is important to choose a real estate agent who can answer your questions quickly and clearly.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also benefit from our article <a title="Couchsurfing and Airbnb Experiences for Students in Turkey" href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Couchsurfing and Airbnb Experiences for Students in Turkey</a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="common-problems-you-may-encounter-while-working-with-real-estate-agents">Common Problems You May Encounter While Working with Real Estate Agents</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When working with real estate agents, you may encounter some common problems. Knowing these issues in advance will make the process go more smoothly:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Misinformation:</strong> Real estate agents can sometimes give misleading information about the condition or price of a property. Therefore, always do your own research.</li>



<li><strong>Contract Issues:</strong> Contracts with real estate agents can be complicated. Read the contract carefully and ask about anything you do not understand.</li>



<li><strong>Communication Gaps:</strong> If you are having trouble communicating with your real estate agent, be aware that the process may slow down. It is important to keep communication channels open.</li>



<li><strong>Service Fees:</strong> Service fees of real estate agents may vary. Clarify in advance how much the service fee will be.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Also <a title="On-Campus vs. Off-Campus Living: Cost Analysis" href="https://roadtostudy.com/">On-Campus vs. You can also take a look at Off-Campus Living: Cost Analysis</a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="realtor-fees-and-contracts-what-you-need-to-know">Realtor Fees and Contracts: What You Need to Know</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When working with a real estate agent, it is important to know about fees and contracts. Here are the points you should pay attention to:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Service Fee:</strong> Note that real estate agents usually charge a commission of 2-3% of the purchase and sale price. However, this rate may vary depending on the experience and service of the real estate agent.</li>



<li><strong>Contract Terms:</strong> Carefully read the terms stated in the contract. Cancellation conditions, length of service and other details are important.</li>



<li><strong>Extra Fees:</strong> When working with a real estate agent, additional fees may be charged for additional services (marketing, photography, etc.). Be clear about this.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="information-on-visa-and-residence-permits-in-the-real-estate-process-in-turkey">Information on Visa and Residence Permits in the Real Estate Process in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Visa and residence permits are an important issue for foreigners who want to buy real estate in Turkey. Here&#8217;s what you need to know:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Residence Permit in Real Estate Purchase:</strong> Foreigners who purchase real estate in Turkey can obtain a residence permit if they meet certain conditions. This process can be guided by your real estate agent.</li>



<li><strong>Visa Application:</strong> Foreigners who wish to stay in Turkey for a long period of time must first apply for a visa. The required documents may also include a real estate title deed.</li>



<li><strong>Legal Processes:</strong> During the real estate purchase process, be informed about legal processes such as notary procedures and title deed transfer. Your real estate agent will help you with this.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="choose-your-realtor-correctly-relax">Choose Your Realtor Correctly, Relax!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Working with real estate agents in Turkey can offer great advantages when the right steps are taken. Being careful when choosing a real estate agent, knowing the problems you may encounter in advance and clarifying the terms of the contract will make the process go more smoothly. Turkey offers attractive opportunities for investors with its dynamic real estate market. This guide will help you make more informed decisions by providing you with important information during the real estate buying process in Turkey. Remember, you can make the most of this process with good planning and the right information at every step.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-should-i-look-for-when-choosing-a-real-estate-agent">What should I look for when choosing a real estate agent?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When choosing a real estate agent, you should pay attention to factors such as license, experience, references and communication skills.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-much-are-real-estate-agent-fees">How much are real estate agent fees?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The service fee of real estate agents is usually 2-3% of the purchase and sale price, and this rate may vary depending on the experience of the real estate agent.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-are-the-problems-i-may-encounter-when-working-with-real-estate-agents">What are the problems I may encounter when working with real estate agents?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You may encounter problems such as misinformation, contractual issues, lack of communication and service fees.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="can-i-get-a-residence-permit-for-buying-real-estate-in-turkey">Can I get a residence permit for buying real estate in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, foreigners who buy real estate in Turkey can obtain a residence permit if they meet certain conditions.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="when-should-i-apply-for-a-visa">When should I apply for a visa?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It is recommended that you apply for your visa at least 3 months before you arrive in Turkey. The application process usually takes 2-4 weeks.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-08-27T14:46:16Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T18:51:49Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/things-to-consider-when-working-with-real-estate-agents.webp","alt":"University student shaking hands with a real estate agent in a sunlit modern apartment, one holding a key","title":"things-to-consider-when-working-with-real-estate-agents"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'working-with-real-estate-agents';
