</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="discover-the-most-favorable-shipping-prices-now-take-advantage">Discover the most favorable shipping prices now, take advantage!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey is a country that offers a wide range of cargo and courier services. It is possible to find affordable and reliable services for international students. By considering the factors that affect costs, you can choose the most suitable shipping company for your needs. With the information we have provided in this article, you can make more informed decisions about cargo and courier services in Turkey. Remember, every shipping process can be made easier with the right planning and knowledge.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How long are the shipping times?</h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Cargo delivery times vary depending on the type of service selected and the distance. Standard shipments usually arrive within 3-7 business days, while express shipments arrive within 1-3 business days.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Are there additional fees when shipping abroad?</h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, there may be additional fees such as customs duties and insurance. It is important to research these additional costs before shipping.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-should-i-choose-between-shipping-companies">How should I choose between shipping companies?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When choosing a shipping company, you should consider price, service quality, customer reviews and shipping times.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How much does shipping cost to Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Shipping a 20 kg parcel to Turkey varies by origin. From <strong>Europe (e.g., Germany)</strong>, it costs approximately <strong>€30–€50</strong> via DHL. From the <strong>UK</strong>, expect to pay around <strong>£50–£80</strong> using economy services like Parcelforce. From the <strong>USA</strong>, rates are significantly higher, often exceeding <strong>$150–$250</strong> with carriers like FedEx or UPS.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the cost of air cargo per kg?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Air cargo rates for larger commercial shipments (freight) generally range from <strong>$3.00 to $7.00 USD per kg</strong>. For example, importing from China to Turkey averages <strong>$4.50–$7.00/kg</strong>, while exporting from Turkey to Europe (like Germany or UK) is often cheaper, around <strong>€1.10–€2.00/kg</strong> for shipments over 100 kg.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-01-18T09:28:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T18:39:35Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/shipping-and-courier-service-costs-in-turkey.webp","alt":"A delivery truck and courier handing over a package in a Turkish city street.","title":"shipping-and-courier-service-costs-in-turkey"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'cargo-courier-services-costs-in-turkey' );
